 Optics Plus Eye Centre,Festac Town, Lagos ,is offering free eye and glaucoma tests  to enable people know their visual status. The offer is to mark the World Glaucoma Week 2020  which runs between March 8 and 14 and help in preventing more cases of blindness. Glaucoma, according to WHO, is the second leading cause of blindness in the world. Early detection of glaucoma, like most illnesses,  helps to manage it properly. The centre said blindness can be prevented if properly diagnosed at the early stages. 